    "problemStatement": "You are given an array AAA consisting of NNN positive integers.\n\nFind \u2211i=1N\u2211j=iNF3(i,j)\\sum_{i=1}^{N} \\sum_{j=i}^{N} F^3(i,j)\u2211i=1N\u200b\u2211j=iN\u200bF3(i,j), where F(i,j)=\u2211k=ijAkF(i,j)=\\sum_{k=i}^{j} A_kF(i,j)=\u2211k=ij\u200bAk\u200b.\n\nSince the value might be quite large, print it modulo 998244353998244353998244353.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input contains a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of two lines of input.\n\nThe first line of each test case contains an integer NNN \u2014 the length of the array AAA.\nThe second line of each test case contains NNN space-separated integers A1,A2,\u2026,ANA_1,A_2,\\ldots,A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b representing the array AAA.\n\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line, the answer, modulo 998244353998244353998244353.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641051 \\leq T \\leq 10^51\u2264T\u2264105",
      "1\u2264N\u22645\u22c51051 \\leq N \\leq 5 \\cdot 10^51\u2264N\u22645\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264Ai\u22641061 \\leq A_i \\leq 10^61\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264106",
      "The sum of NNN over all test cases won't exceed 5\u22c51055 \\cdot 10^55\u22c5105."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "3\n2\n1 1\n3\n1 2 1\n5\n8 5 6 2 3",
        "output": "10\n128\n42621",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest case 111: F(1,1)=1,F(1,2)=1+1=2,F(2,2)=1F(1, 1) = 1, F(1, 2) = 1+1=2, F(2, 2) = 1F(1,1)=1,F(1,2)=1+1=2,F(2,2)=1.\nThus, \u2211i=1N\u2211j=iNF3(i,j)=13+23+13=10\\sum_{i=1}^{N} \\sum_{j=i}^{N} F^3(i,j) = 1^3 + 2^3 + 1^3 = 10\u2211i=1N\u200b\u2211j=iN\u200bF3(i,j)=13+23+13=10.\nTest case 222: F(1,1)=1,F(1,2)=1+2=3,F(1,3)=1+2+1=4,F(2,2)=2,F(2,3)=2+1=3,F(3,3)=1F(1, 1) = 1, F(1, 2) = 1+2=3, F(1, 3) = 1+2+1 =4, F(2, 2) = 2, F(2, 3) = 2+1=3, F(3, 3) = 1F(1,1)=1,F(1,2)=1+2=3,F(1,3)=1+2+1=4,F(2,2)=2,F(2,3)=2+1=3,F(3,3)=1.\nThus, \u2211i=1N\u2211j=iNF3(i,j)=13+33+43+23+33+13=128\\sum_{i=1}^{N} \\sum_{j=i}^{N} F^3(i,j) = 1^3 + 3^3 + 4^3+2^3+3^3+1^3 = 128\u2211i=1N\u200b\u2211j=iN\u200bF3(i,j)=13+33+43+23+33+13=128."
      }
    ]
